Trait description: verticillium wilt disease severity is the percentage of relevant host tissues or organ covered by symptom or lesion or damaged by the disease. Severity results from the number and size of the lesions.
Method description: verticillium wilt severity (or disease infection index) is calculated according to the formula: DI=[?(Ni ◊ i)/(N ◊ i)] ◊ 100, Where i is the maximum disease grade, Ni, the number of plants with corresponding disease grade and N the number of total investigated plants.
